{"type":"message","id":"a6630457","parentId":"16519ea7","timestamp":"2026-04-28T09:34:02.025Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now section 3 - Bible Verse.","thinkingSignature":"b3d55f68ba4f39eebb482501ea28af033c24a1882575a16988727525efe31d1f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xhcy7pqx4c4n_1","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","channel":"telegram","target":"8212808444","message":"📖 BIBLE VERSE OF THE DAY\n\n\"Your attitude should be the same as that of Christ Jesus: Who, being in very nature God, did not consider equality with God something to be grasped, but made himself nothing, taking the very nature of a servant, being made in human likeness. And being found in appearance as a man, he humbled himself and became obedient to death — even death on a cross!\"\n— Philippians 2:5-8 (NIV)\n\n💡 TODAY'S MOTIVATION: What a powerful reminder to start your week with humility and servant's heart. With your schedule light today — just Chase at 9 AM — you've got space to lead with patience and presence. Whether it's a quick reply to Angelina at Walkway Realty about that apartment lead, or just being fully where you are with Logan — let humility be the move of the day. You've got a free day on your calendar, so resist the urge to fill it. Rest flows from trust, not hustle."}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12168,"output":268,"cacheRead":20865,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33301,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777368833788,"responseId":"063fb2012d3058fbb65250ae7a1f960d"}}
